Bill Weld and I are the alternative you can be proud of
8/ Honest, transparent, and honorable
7/ The only ticket to include successful governors (and former Republican governors of Democratic-leaning states, at that)
6/ We'll stop the polarization, call out both sides, and bring America together
5/ The only advocates for free trade
4/ Skeptical of our military interventions
3/ Socially inclusive
2/ Fiscally conservative
1/ Why America should elect Bill Weld and me:
There's total denial of the entitlement issues here. And they could be the biggest issues facing our country. America deserves better.
Entitlements! With under a minute to go!
Not addressing the debt related to Medicare, Medicaid, and Social Security is NOT an option.
The whopper of the evening, @HillaryClinton: "I'm not going to add a penny to the debt."
Kudos to Chris Wallace for bringing up the topic they don't want to talk about: wasteful spending and debt. Wish we had more than 4 mins!
A balanced budget demonstrates our commitment to young people. Politicians' debt is unfairly a burden on younger generations. #debate
Bill Weld and I promise to submit a balanced budget to Congress in the first 100 days in office #debate
ISIS is in part the result of a vacuum created by regime change in Iraq--a policy both @HillaryClinton and @realDonaldTrump supported.
We need better judgment on foreign policy. I opposed the Iraq War and would not put our young people in harm's way unless attacked. #debate
Let's get real. BOTH @realDonaldTrump and @HillaryClinton supported the war in Iraq. Now they want to cover up their mistakes.
"Element of surprise" in this case would have cost a lot of civilian lives #Mosul #debate
We do have boots on the ground in Mosul (special forces) #debate
We've been issue-free for a while in this #debate when we should be talking about #jobs, foreign policy, #economy, personal #liberty
Let's bring America together and end this divisiveness. There IS another way. #debate
Good government is easy. Bill and I did it in our states. #debate
We've returned to the scandal vs. scandal portion of the #debate
I would sign #TPP because free trade on net leads to more US #jobs. Higher tariffs (taxes) means more poverty and fewer jobs.
.@HillaryClinton, everything you say adds to the debt #debate
"Investments" (n): Bigger government from @HillaryClinton #DebateDictionary
The isolationism of @realDonaldTrump is stunning. "Going our own way" on trade means more taxes on you and me.
"Regime"? The presidency is now a "regime"? Yikes.
We have our first agreement of the night! More debt! The @realDonaldTrump plan =$10T more the @HillaryClinton plan=$20T more #debate
Support #smallbusiness AND raise the #minimumwage... that's definitely a contradiction in terms. #debate
When you bring certainty that taxes will not go up, that rules and regs won't become worse, #jobs will increase. #debate
We have bombed seven Muslim countries in the last year. It doesn't appear that'll change with these two. #debate
(And release your tax returns, @realDonaldTrump)
Being President is an incredible responsibility and honor. It requires #transparency. Release the speeches, @HillaryClinton. #debates
We would have more context on @HillaryClinton's @GoldmanSachs speeches if we didn't have to rely on @wikileaks. She can solve that problem!
#Debate note: apparently, @realDonaldTrump is upset that @POTUS didn't break up more families and deport more undocumented workers.
Make it as easy as possible to get a work visa that would entail a background check and a SSN card (so taxes are paid). #debate
If @HillaryClinton + her party wanted to solve immigration problems, they could have done it when they controlled government. They didn't.
Let's build economic bridges to #Mexico, not walls. #debate

Don't build a wall across the border. It's insanity. #debate
